[mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, - generated `literals` for each service - auto discovery of types for `boto3.client` and `boto3.resource` calls - auto discovery of types for `session.client` and `session.resource` calls - auto discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in [releases](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder/releases). ## versioning documentation_summary: The HTML text is a PyPI (Python Package Index) project page for "types-aiobotocore-lex-models" version 2.12.1, released on March 5, 2024. This package provides type annotations for the aiobotocore.LexModelBuildingService 2.12.1 service, generated with mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.2, aimed at enhancing code quality and developer productivity by enabling better autocomplete and error detection features in various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright. It requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The package supports a wide range of Python versions from 3.8 to 3.13 and is maintained by Vlad Emelianov. The project emphasizes compatibility with mypy and pyright for type checking, offering detailed documentation and support for contributing to further development.
